snippet.title: Animal Crossing: New Horizons – Nintendo Switch 2 Edition & Free Update – Announcement Trailer
snippet.description:
The Animal Crossing: New Horizons – Nintendo Switch 2 Edition game and a free update to the base game launch January 15, 2026. Only on the Nintendo Switch 2 and Nintendo Switch systems. Pre-orders are coming soon! Learn more: https://www.nintendo.com/us/store/products/animal-crossing-new-horizons-nintendo-switch-2-edition-upgrade-pack-switch-2/?utm_source=DLC&utm_medium=soytnoa&utm_campaign=S1017-01&utm_id=S1017-01
  
With enhanced resolution, mouse controls using the Joy-Con 2 controller, expanded online play*, and more features exclusive to Nintendo Switch 2, players can get even more out of the island life in Animal Crossing: New Horizons – Nintendo Switch 2 Edition! 
  
Plus, a free update is coming to Animal Crossing: New Horizons for players on both Nintendo Switch 2 and Nintendo Switch to enjoy. The free update includes a new resort hotel, additional amiibo** functionality, collaboration items, updates to online play, and more. 
  
We can't wait for you to see everything new on the island January 15, 2026! 
  
Nintendo Switch 2 players who already have Animal Crossing: New Horizons on Nintendo Switch can upgrade to the Nintendo Switch 2 Edition by purchasing the upgrade pack***. 
  
*Nintendo Switch Online membership (sold separately) and Nintendo Account required for online features. Membership auto-renews after initial term at the then-current price unless canceled. Not available in all countries. Internet access required for online features. Terms apply. nintendo.com/purchase-terms/ 
  
**amiibo sold separately. Visit amiibo.com for details on amiibo functionality. 
  
***Full version of Animal Crossing: New Horizons game required to use this content. Sold separately. For details, visit support.nintendo.com/switch2/upgradepack

snippet.title: UPSIDE DOWN (A Hazbin Hotel Song) - Black Gryph0n & Baasik
snippet.description:
STREAM #UPSIDEDOWN ON SPOTIFY: https://open.spotify.com/track/70lG2bwQd9OIaoIWbg0eMH?si=lZ7PDIkTR_Gwuf_9o-wa0A&nd=1&_branch_match_id=link-1512788054174522531

AND EVERYWHERE ELSE: https://ffm.to/bgb-upsidedown

Official Karaoke Track on BAASIK'S channel! https://youtu.be/wpg7k-Mwf_A?si=TFfCLJGqD4UGthyr

MORE ORIGINAL MUSIC HERE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PrMjrvz5hyc&list=PLv1P-6YxEm6AgF6yiKtydFevNQV4RxKn4&index=1

OMG I can't believe we did ANOTHER Hazbin Hotel song! I thought we were done after Daisies, but Nate and I got to talking about the new season and Alastor's backstory and we had this idea... we just had to make a song about it!
Then Lux came in with her genius visual storytelling, and that was that! I hope y'all like it! It's one of my new faves!

CREDITS:


Written by Gabe & Nate brown (Black Gryph0n & Baasik)

Produced by Nate Brown (Baasik): https://www.youtube.com/user/Baasikmusic

Performed by Gabriel Brown (Black Gryph0n): https://www.youtube.com/c/BlackGryph0n

Animated by Luximus: https://youtube.com/@Luximus17?si=xzByJGFs_3R5mcpa (https://youtube.com/@Luximus17?si=xzByJGFs_3R5mcpa)



-- --- ---- ----- Lyrics ----- ---- --- --


“With your smile, turn the world upside down”

Sit down, I’m gonna tell ya
A little story ‘bout a sad little fella
He was a Dapper-Dan Cinderella
Oh, and lemme tell ya
It made the other fellas jealous

They made him cry
“Na na na”
Spit in his eye
“Ha ha ha”
How could they pick on such a friendly little guy?

This town was kinda broken
Not the kind of place you’d leave your doors open
Full of backwards, back-woods broke-men
Still he was copin’
Yeah he was dreamin’ hopin’

He’d get away
“Na na na”
Maybe someday
“Ha ha ha”
But on the radio his momma used to play.

“When it feels like all the world is wearing a frown
Put a smile on and spread it around.”

With your smile, turn the world upside down.

CHORUS:
Da da, da da da da
Da da da da da dada

Well now he had the spirit
And he would smile every time he’d hear it
Soon he knew every single lyric
Oh, and he would sing it
And in his sleep he’d dream it

All day and night
“Na na na”
Through every fight
“La La La”
You wouldn’t judge him if you knew what it was like

And how, as luck would have it
He got rewarded for his weird new habit
He earned a fat green stack of cabbage
And he planned to stash it
Till he was livin’ lavish

That fateful day
“Na na na”
He ran away
“La La La”
And he could hear the song his momma used to play

“When it feels like all the world is wearing a frown
Put a smile on and spread it around…”

With his smile, he’d turn the world upside down!

Chorus:
Da da, da da da da
Da da da da da dada

When it feels like all the world is wearing a frown
Put a smile on and spread it around.

With my smile, I turned the world upside down.


- -- --- ---- ----- END ----- ---- --- -- -

Hello DDR’s (dedicated description readers)

You guys, we have been going NON-STOP but it's all GOOD (except for yesterday, that was kinda scary) but everything else is good! Lots of new music, but we can't show you yet because it's all in stuff that we don't own... but hopefully we'll be able to show you soon!

Anyway, yesterday I went to Eugene to test-fly an airplane and had a complete loss of coms. Had to squawk 7600 and make my way to the runway via light-signal (first time for everything). Turns out the alternator was off and the battery died. The landing was also less-than-pretty and the wheel fairings were a bit too tight, so when we touched down, they sorta exploded. They had to shut down the runway and do a FOD walk to pick up the chunks of fiberglass! There were firetrucks and everything (fortunately, not necessary). Not my favorite test flight, but a good story!

Oh yeah, we recorded some new stuff for Billie Bust Up and guys... this game is going to blow your socks off. I really don't think I can overstate it. I can't WAIT for this game to come out!

OK, that's all I have time for. My wife is eepy but also wants to watch a movie, so I gotta go do that before she falls asleep and I have to carry her to bed. My back only has a few more of those trips left in it...

LOVE Y'ALL!!

~Gabe

snippet.title: 𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐆𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐃𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐨𝐲𝐞𝐝 𝐌𝐲 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞.
snippet.description:
Europa Universalis 5 is about to be released and I have been playing it for nearly 6 months and finally get to share my experiences with the world! This is the biggest strategy game release of the year and so we have been graciously sponsored by Paradox Interactive to create this video on a game that I 100% would have made a video on anyway because its my perfect cup of tea. 

You Can Purchase the game here: https://paradoxinteractive.i38e.net/6y4ovq
(Use code "Spiffing" At checkout)
(Might be cheaper than steam in your local currency)

So what is EU5, rather simply this game is a 4X grand strategy game set between 5 centuries of human history starting in the late medieval leading into things like the renaissance and era of exploration filled with colonisation and discovery. Paradox on steam describe the game as so: Use war, trade or diplomacy to satisfy your grandest ambitions and dominate five centuries of history in the newest version of Europa Universalis, Paradox Interactive's flagship historical grand strategy game.

I think its a pretty darn accurate representation of the game as trade war and diplomacy make up the foundational pillars of this strategy game. However today I am not intending to play the game in a way that was intended. I am not playing as England and winning the 100 years war against France, NO! I am playing as the hanseatic league. The Single most overpowered nation in all of EU5. Today I will show you how to make big money, make a big empire and how to become the worlds leading economic great power! 

Chapters:
00:00 - Intro
02:20 - Chapter 1: The Basics
05:44 - Setting up our Trade Routes
09:14 - Our new Best Friend
12:23 - Bullying the Tuscans
18:44 - To War!
20:27 - Chapter 2: The Black Death
22:55 - When you beat them, Join them!
28:07 - The Trade Snowball
31:01 - Chapter 3: The Climb
33:32 - The Road to Number 1!
36:26 - All Hail the Hanseatic League!
38:47 - Outro & Thanks for Watching!

The Spiffing Brit Vs EU5 - 2025s Hardest Strategy Game Is Perfectly Balanced

snippet.title: The Day After Tomorrow 2 (2025) - Teaser Trailer | Jake Gyllenhaal
snippet.description:
#dayaftertomorrow2 #jakegyllenhaal #disaster

Jake Gyllenhaal rumored to return for The Day After Tomorrow 2.

Editing, VFX, SFX, Thumbnail by @KHStudio please subscribe:
✅ YouTube: https://bit.ly/KHstudio

🎥 Attention viewers!

Please note that this video is a concept trailer created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes. I have meticulously incorporated various effects, sound design, AI technologies (Google Veo 3), movie analytics, and other elements to bring my vision to life. Its purpose is purely artistic, aiming to entertain and engage with the YouTube community. My goal is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through this trailer. Thank you for your support, and let's dive into the world of imagination! 🍿

🌍 The Day After Tomorrow 2

Talk suggests Jake Gyllenhaal’s character may return as a scientist tasked with navigating a new environmental crisis, this time an even larger-scale, catastrophic event that threatens the planet’s very survival. The stakes are higher as global warming accelerates, and the team must race against time to stop the weather from spiraling completely out of control.

Fans expect massive, high-octane action set pieces—a flood of water over skyscrapers, mega-storms ravaging cities, and characters racing through collapsing infrastructure. The emotional core will likely focus on humanity’s ability to adapt, rebuild, and survive against nature’s overwhelming force.

Nothing confirmed, but whispers suggest an epic finale, where humanity must decide whether they can recover or are doomed to repeat the cycle.

Feel free to express your thoughts on this exciting project by leaving a comment below.
